Italy sold benchmark three- and 10-
year bonds and borrowing costs declined in the countryâ€™s final
debt sale of the year.  The Treasury in  Rome  sold 6 percent bonds due in 2014 to
yield 5.62 percent, down from 7.89 percent at the previous sale
on Nov. 29 and priced its 5 percent 2022 bond to yield 6.98
percent, compared with 7.56 percent on Nov. 29.  The Treasury
also sold bonds due in 2021 and a floating-rate security due
2018.  To contact the reporter on this story:
